Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.27,0:00:10.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Cease what you are\Ndoing and gaze at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.33,0:00:14.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Stop everything, save for\Nthe thrumming of your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.26,0:00:17.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Theft. It is an\Nespecially sweet vice,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.31,0:00:19.21,Main,,0,0,0,,more elegant than vandalism
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.23,0:00:21.42,Main,,0,0,0,,and more complex\Nthan simple robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.20,0:00:25.41,Main,,0,0,0,,A beautiful blend of secrets\Nand crime and mischief and fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.43,0:00:27.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Like dear Heathcliff,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.38,0:00:30.35,Main,,0,0,0,,I am defined by my\Nall-consuming passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.37,0:00:33.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Stealing is my greatest\Ncarnal pleasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.29,0:00:35.38,Main,,0,0,0,,a pleasure for which\NI will risk my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.40,0:00:38.34,Main,,0,0,0,,a sexy prison from\Nwhich there is no escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.36,0:00:41.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Why am I this way?\NWho can know?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.36,0:00:44.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Who is the slave and\Nwho's the master?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.29,0:00:47.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Do divine eyes fall\Nupon me any longer,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.24,0:00:48.40,Main,,0,0,0,,or have the given up?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.42,0:00:51.40,Main,,0,0,0,,The rush of a theft\Nallows me to forget all,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.42,0:00:55.20,Main,,0,0,0,,and yet to distantly\Nremember all, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.30,0:01:03.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Run and speak not.\NHide and run not.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.28,0:01:05.35,Main,,0,0,0,,When you've found\Nme, punish me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.37,0:01:09.32,Main,,0,0,0,,When you've punished\Nme, kill me. Save me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.25,0:01:15.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Little boy, there is nothing\Nleft to steal from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.29,0:01:21.22,Main,,0,0,0,,You have long been an\Nempty shell. Just as I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.24,0:01:25.21,Main,,0,0,0,,And so, if you would gaze at\Nme, cease what you are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.23,0:01:29.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Stop everything save for the\Nthrumming of your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.35,0:01:48.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.21,0:01:51.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Where's the excitement\Nin swiping something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.31,0:01:53.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Such a gaudy piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.33,0:01:58.38,Main,,0,0,0,,It's plenty exciting, Lupin.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.40,0:02:01.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Nothing looks gaudy if you\Nknow the right way to wear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.42,0:02:04.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Besides, every treasure\Nis further proof of how
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.28,0:02:06.25,Main,,0,0,0,,exceptional I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.27,0:02:09.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess there's\Nno arguing with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.21,0:02:16.20,Main,,0,0,0,,So, why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.22,0:02:18.28,Main,,0,0,0,,I got you a little something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.26,0:02:24.37,Main,,0,0,0,,This is a straightforward\Napproach for a man like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.39,0:02:27.33,Main,,0,0,0,,I thought you would\Nenjoy a gem rose bouquet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.35,0:02:29.22,Main,,0,0,0,,They are pretty enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.24,0:02:31.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Although, red does tend\Nto be a overdone choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.36,0:02:32.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.37,0:02:34.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Then please, allow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.27,0:02:40.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Ah, alexandrite,\Nit's color is dictated
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.32,0:02:42.20,Main,,0,0,0,,by the light that hits it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.22,0:02:44.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Appears blue when seen\Nby sunlight and turns red
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.40,0:02:49.26,Main,,0,0,0,,in fire light. Pretty princely\Ngift, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.28,0:02:51.38,Main,,0,0,0,,This pays for\Nthe peep show you got.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.40,0:02:53.39,Main,,0,0,0,,But you'd need the\Nbiggest alexandrite stone
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.41,0:02:55.42,Main,,0,0,0,,there is to have\Na shot with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.20,0:02:57.26,Main,,0,0,0,,The biggest one?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.28,0:02:59.35,Main,,0,0,0,,The one they've got in\Nthe Smithsonian, you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.37,0:03:01.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Drive a hard bargain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.20,0:03:03.28,Main,,0,0,0,,You keep raising\Nthe bar like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.30,0:03:05.26,Main,,0,0,0,,and you just might\Ntrip over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.28,0:03:07.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the friendly warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.41,0:03:12.21,Main,,0,0,0,,So, you really\Nwant me that badly?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.23,0:03:14.25,Main,,0,0,0,,The threats I make\Nare never empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.27,0:03:17.37,Main,,0,0,0,,When I say I'm gonna\Nsteal something, I mean it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.39,0:03:20.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Then I have a\Nproposal for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.31,0:03:22.22,Main,,0,0,0,,You've heard all about\Nthe new pyramid
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.24,0:03:24.32,Main,,0,0,0,,they discovered\Nin Egypt, I take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.34,0:03:27.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the one that was\Nhidden under the sand?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.27,0:03:30.34,Main,,0,0,0,,That's the official line but\Nunofficially, illegal diggers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.36,0:03:33.24,Main,,0,0,0,,have known of its\Nexistence for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.26,0:03:36.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Criminals have always been in\Nthe know before anybody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.25,0:03:38.37,Main,,0,0,0,,It's been like that\Nfor centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.39,0:03:41.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Have you heard about a certain\Ntreasure said to be inside:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.34,0:03:43.32,Main,,0,0,0,,the red-feathered\NLaughing Peacock?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.34,0:03:46.37,Main,,0,0,0,,I've heard rumors\Nabout it, but nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.39,0:03:48.40,Main,,0,0,0,,According to legend,\Nwhoever gets their hands
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.42,0:03:52.31,Main,,0,0,0,,on that peacock will\Nbecome rich beyond belief.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.37,0:04:02.38,Main,,0,0,0,,"On one side of the scale\Nis the Feather of Ma'at,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.40,0:04:05.38,Main,,0,0,0,,the goddess of truth. The\Ndeceased places his own heart
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.40,0:04:09.40,Main,,0,0,0,,on the other side of\Nthe scale to weigh it."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.42,0:04:13.27,Main,,0,0,0,,"If his sins in life were heavy,\Nthe scales will tip. This is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.29,0:04:17.27,Main,,0,0,0,,a sign that the deceased will\Nnever be reborn into the world."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.29,0:04:20.32,Main,,0,0,0,,"The ritual is known as\Nthe Judgment of the Dead."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.24,0:04:28.24,Main,,0,0,0,,You know better than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.26,0:04:30.22,Main,,0,0,0,,There's notelling what\Nthat scary man will do
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.24,0:04:31.38,Main,,0,0,0,,if you get too close.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.40,0:04:34.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.29,0:04:36.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Guess it doesn't\Nmatter where I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.35,0:04:38.36,Main,,0,0,0,,There's no hiding my past.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.38,0:04:40.39,Main,,0,0,0,,It's written on my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.42,0:04:46.22,Main,,0,0,0,,It's not like I came here\Nthinking I would be reborn
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.24,0:04:48.37,Main,,0,0,0,,or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.39,0:04:51.20,Main,,0,0,0,,But can't a guy catch a break?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.36,0:04:57.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.39,0:05:00.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.22,0:05:02.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Wanna know what\Nyour sins weigh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.29,0:05:04.23,Main,,0,0,0,,It won't cost too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.25,0:05:06.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Against a feather,\NI'm guessing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.26,0:05:09.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Like a real-world version of\Nthe Judgment of the Dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.27,0:05:10.39,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't have to tell\Nthe story, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.41,0:05:12.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.29,0:05:14.25,Main,,0,0,0,,You can see they're\Nthe same weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.27,0:05:16.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Now all you have to do\Nis pick up the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.40,0:05:19.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Think of your past sins and\Nthen put it back on the scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.34,0:05:22.28,Main,,0,0,0,,And what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.30,0:05:23.41,Main,,0,0,0,,It magically changes weight?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.43,0:05:26.20,Main,,0,0,0,,'Cause that would be\Nso difficult to rig.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.22,0:05:27.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you afraid?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.30,0:05:29.42,Main,,0,0,0,,You must've done\Nsome pretty rotten stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.20,0:05:31.21,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.23,0:05:32.35,Main,,0,0,0,,I can tell just by your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.30,0:05:41.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.42,0:05:43.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Not so fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.21,0:05:45.35,Main,,0,0,0,,This your partner? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.30,0:05:51.41,Main,,0,0,0,,You little!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.38,0:05:59.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Even the monkey was in on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.24,0:06:01.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Least there's one thing\Nthey didn't get.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.27,0:06:07.35,Main,,0,0,0,,This is little better than\Na hunk of scrap metal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.37,0:06:10.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Besides, don't you\Nneed it to make a living?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.42,0:06:12.34,Main,,0,0,0,,No way you can go straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.36,0:06:14.20,Main,,0,0,0,,That's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.22,0:06:15.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.38,0:06:17.23,Main,,0,0,0,,You know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.25,0:06:20.23,Main,,0,0,0,,If it's money you need,\NI might be able to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.25,0:06:24.23,Main,,0,0,0,,I've got a job that would be\Nright up your alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.28,0:06:34.24,Main,,0,0,0,,You want me to steal\Nthe--what was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.26,0:06:35.38,Main,,0,0,0,,The Laughing Peacock?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.40,0:06:38.40,Main,,0,0,0,,There are a great many people\Neager to get their hands on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.42,0:06:41.27,Main,,0,0,0,,That peacock has become\Nthe stuff of legend among
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.29,0:06:43.41,Main,,0,0,0,,the inhabitants of\Nthis city's underworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.43,0:06:46.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Story goes that when\Nits feathers shine crimson,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.43,0:06:48.36,Main,,0,0,0,,it will bestow great riches.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.38,0:06:50.27,Main,,0,0,0,,That sounds pretty formulaic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.29,0:06:51.35,Main,,0,0,0,,What do you expect?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.37,0:06:53.37,Main,,0,0,0,,That's how legends tend to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.39,0:06:56.30,Main,,0,0,0,,There are some\Nvariations to the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.32,0:06:57.39,Main,,0,0,0,,One version says that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.41,0:07:01.32,Main,,0,0,0,,when the peacock's feathers\Nare blue, death is near.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.29,0:07:18.31,Main,,0,0,0,,An old well leads inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.33,0:07:22.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Few who have entered have\Never come back out alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.39,0:07:26.38,Main,,0,0,0,,They say there's a curse\Naround every corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.29,0:07:37.36,Main,,0,0,0,,I guess that guy was after\Nthe Laughing Peacock, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.37,0:07:50.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Blasphemous trespasser.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.37,0:07:55.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Leave now while you\Nstill have your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.27,0:07:56.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.30,0:07:58.34,Main,,0,0,0,,An oil spray set alight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.36,0:08:01.35,Main,,0,0,0,,An oil drawing of\Na pharaoh on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.37,0:08:04.23,Main,,0,0,0,,And a well-placed\Nloud speaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.30,0:08:08.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Neat trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.26,0:08:22.32,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm definitely not\Nthe only one in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.34,0:08:24.37,Main,,0,0,0,,There's no curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.39,0:08:26.35,Main,,0,0,0,,It's just the tomb raiders.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.37,0:08:29.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Each man out to\Nprotect his own loot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.31,0:08:35.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Leave now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.37,0:08:37.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Or face the consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.36,0:08:42.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you deaf? I said, leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.39,0:08:56.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.28,0:08:58.43,Main,,0,0,0,,This is the thanks I get for\Ngiving you such a kind warning?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.21,0:09:02.22,Main,,0,0,0,,You're gonna pay dearly for\Nbeing a grave robber, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.24,0:09:03.31,Main,,0,0,0,,What, and you're not?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.33,0:09:04.31,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.33,0:09:06.26,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm just a generic robber.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.28,0:09:09.40,Main,,0,0,0,,A pro among pros; I specialize\Nin hard to get items.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.42,0:09:12.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Pretty petty tactics\Nfor someone so professional.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.40,0:09:15.35,Main,,0,0,0,,I thought you might\Nlike some entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.37,0:09:17.32,Main,,0,0,0,,This next question's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.34,0:09:19.39,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you here to steal?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.41,0:09:21.21,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.23,0:09:22.35,Main,,0,0,0,,What if I said a peacock?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.37,0:09:24.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Bad answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.37,0:09:31.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Back where we started.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.25,0:09:35.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Three.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.21,0:09:37.41,Main,,0,0,0,,And two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.43,0:09:39.21,Main,,0,0,0,,One!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.23,0:09:39.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Zero
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.37,0:09:57.20,Main,,0,0,0,,I take it this isn't\None of your traps?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.22,0:09:58.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.23,0:10:00.35,Main,,0,0,0,,My work's a lot\Nclassier than this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.37,0:10:02.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, drop the gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.32,0:10:05.30,Main,,0,0,0,,I've never known a Magnum\Nto fire a seventh round.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.32,0:10:07.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Or a Walther to fire a tenth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.30,0:10:13.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Uh oh--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.35,0:11:20.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.30,0:12:10.32,Main,,0,0,0,,That's some lousy art.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.24,0:12:21.24,Main,,0,0,0,,It's a dead-end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.27,0:12:27.20,Main,,0,0,0,,This again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.37,0:12:33.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Looks like something goes here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.31,0:12:45.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Like a hand with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.40,0:12:48.23,Main,,0,0,0,,So you did make it out alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.25,0:12:50.30,Main,,0,0,0,,You really should return\Nthe things you borrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.32,0:12:52.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, people will\Nthink you're a thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.33,0:12:53.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.37,0:12:54.32,Main,,0,0,0,,And what do they think\Nabout somebody who
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.34,0:12:56.34,Main,,0,0,0,,messes with another man's ammo?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.41,0:13:00.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Here's a free tip.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.27,0:13:03.23,Main,,0,0,0,,I found a neat trick\Nto getting past traps safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.25,0:13:05.37,Main,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is let a\Nhotshot gunslinger lead the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.39,0:13:07.40,Main,,0,0,0,,and then you're\Nas good as gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.42,0:13:11.20,Main,,0,0,0,,My explosive shells saved\Nyour sorry hide, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.22,0:13:12.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Those babies are top-notch.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.30,0:13:14.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Explode only on impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.41,0:13:17.25,Main,,0,0,0,,You could've at least\Nreloaded all six.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.27,0:13:20.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Sorry about that, but five\Nshells was all I had on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.37,0:13:22.34,Main,,0,0,0,,None of your fancy little\Ntricks are gonna help you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.36,0:13:24.33,Main,,0,0,0,,open this lid, are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.26,0:13:27.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Like I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.35,0:13:29.27,Main,,0,0,0,,You were waiting for me\N'cause you don't have a clue
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.29,0:13:31.27,Main,,0,0,0,,how to open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.29,0:13:33.21,Main,,0,0,0,,See that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.23,0:13:35.27,Main,,0,0,0,,I think that scale\Nis the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.43,0:13:41.21,Main,,0,0,0,,The weight of\Na person's sins, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.23,0:13:42.34,Main,,0,0,0,,How intriguing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.36,0:13:45.23,Main,,0,0,0,,So it'll open if\Nthe scale balances?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.25,0:13:46.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.25,0:13:47.35,Main,,0,0,0,,But that'll never happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.37,0:13:49.36,Main,,0,0,0,,The scale will\Ntip no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.38,0:13:52.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Not even good people\Nare sinless and us---
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.28,0:13:54.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, you and I are\Nsinners down to the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.37,0:13:56.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.23,0:13:58.29,Main,,0,0,0,,So what is there\Nto be afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.31,0:14:01.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Why would you need some deity\Nto tell you how heavy your sins
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.25,0:14:04.32,Main,,0,0,0,,are when you already know\Nwhat you've done in this life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.34,0:14:07.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Besides, even if you're\Nrewarded with rebirth there's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.23,0:14:10.30,Main,,0,0,0,,no guarantee your new life\Nis gonna be a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.32,0:14:11.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.35,0:14:13.41,Main,,0,0,0,,My future is dark, either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.43,0:14:17.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's just try it out for\Nthe sake of entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.34,0:14:20.29,Main,,0,0,0,,It's all make-believe, so why\Nnot have a little fun with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.31,0:14:22.30,Main,,0,0,0,,There isn't any harm in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.30,0:14:28.40,Main,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.32,0:14:34.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Why, hello there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.38,0:14:36.34,Main,,0,0,0,,And up we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.36,0:14:38.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.37,0:14:44.36,Main,,0,0,0,,It's too steep!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.38,0:14:45.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.35,0:14:47.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Put the mummy on the platform!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.20,0:14:50.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Those are scorpions!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.31,0:14:51.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, poisonous ones!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.31,0:14:55.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Not good!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.36,0:14:57.40,Main,,0,0,0,,It's rigged to make us\Nfall no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.43,0:15:03.33,Main,,0,0,0,,A whirlpool?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.35,0:15:06.43,Main,,0,0,0,,It's been fun, but I think I'd\Nlike to get off the ride now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.21,0:15:08.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.23,0:15:10.22,Main,,0,0,0,,You two don't look so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.24,0:15:11.37,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.39,0:15:13.20,Main,,0,0,0,,You're that woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.22,0:15:13.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.40,0:15:16.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Mister Mini-Magnum.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.29,0:15:18.23,Main,,0,0,0,,I remember you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.25,0:15:19.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Your lower half, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.40,0:15:20.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.20,0:15:22.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me\Nyou slept with this guy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.37,0:15:24.36,Main,,0,0,0,,There's no need to be jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.38,0:15:26.37,Main,,0,0,0,,There's a reason\NI called him Mini-Magnum,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.39,0:15:29.41,Main,,0,0,0,,if you catch my drift.\NIsn't that right, Tiny?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.43,0:15:31.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.25,0:15:33.40,Main,,0,0,0,,There's nothing\N'tiny' about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.42,0:15:36.40,Main,,0,0,0,,This whole time you were just\Nusing me to get past the traps.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.42,0:15:38.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.24,0:15:40.23,Main,,0,0,0,,It would be downright\Ninconsiderate to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.25,0:15:42.34,Main,,0,0,0,,to somebody who was just\Ntrying to get me a present.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.36,0:15:46.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Instead, I took an alternate\Nroute listed in an old
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.27,0:15:48.22,Main,,0,0,0,,grave robber's log.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.24,0:15:51.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Traps along this way are\Nmostly out of commission.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.28,0:15:53.28,Main,,0,0,0,,You love your secrets,\Ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.30,0:15:56.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Take a woman's secrets,\Nand what does she have left?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.23,0:15:58.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Besides, how do you ever\Nhope to win the heart
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.22,0:16:01.30,Main,,0,0,0,,of a princess without\Ntaking a few little risks?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.31,0:16:05.20,Main,,0,0,0,,I made it this far, but I\Ndid need help getting past
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.22,0:16:09.20,Main,,0,0,0,,this last obstacle. It's a\Ntricky one. Works like a juicer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.22,0:16:11.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Fall into that chamber\Nand you'll be pulverized.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.37,0:16:13.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Say what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.41,0:16:15.30,Main,,0,0,0,,The blood of the\Nvictim is infused
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.32,0:16:17.37,Main,,0,0,0,,into the picture\Nof the peacock.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.39,0:16:21.36,Main,,0,0,0,,The bird then spreads its red\Nfeathers and flaps its wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.38,0:16:24.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, the "juicer" will\Nstop after one of you falls.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.41,0:16:27.24,Main,,0,0,0,,So, uh, if you want to\Nlive, I suggest you give
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.26,0:16:29.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Mini-Magnum the old heave ho.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.28,0:16:30.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Bye now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.35,0:16:33.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, Tiny!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.34,0:16:35.24,Main,,0,0,0,,What happened\Nbetween you and her?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.26,0:16:37.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Sounds like more\Nthan's happened to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.37,0:16:39.37,Main,,0,0,0,,That mouth is gonna\Nget you in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.39,0:16:40.42,Main,,0,0,0,,She's the reason you're here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.20,0:16:42.35,Main,,0,0,0,,You came to this\Nhellhole for her?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.37,0:16:45.26,Main,,0,0,0,,And that oughta tell you\Njust how much she's worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.28,0:16:47.34,Main,,0,0,0,,More than any other\Ntreasure that I've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.36,0:16:50.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Seems to me that all she does\Nis go around spreading trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.40,0:16:53.26,Main,,0,0,0,,If there's no trouble,\Nit's not worth stealing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.28,0:16:55.34,Main,,0,0,0,,That's the code of\Nthe Lupin family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.36,0:16:57.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Lupin?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.26,0:17:00.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Then I guess that would make you\Nthe infamous Lupin the Third.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.25,0:17:02.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, it's a good thing\Nyou told me, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.30,0:17:05.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Can't make you a gravestone\Nif I don't know who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.37,0:17:06.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the thought
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.20,0:17:09.33,Main,,0,0,0,,but I've still got\Na lot more life to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.35,0:17:12.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Let me know what you want\Non your tombstone, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.25,0:17:14.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Thing is, I'm not in such\Na hurry to die anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.21,0:17:16.37,Main,,0,0,0,,And I suppose\NI owe that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.39,0:17:17.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.43,0:17:35.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, that's that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.26,0:17:36.40,Main,,0,0,0,,I wonder whose blood\Nis going to dye those
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.42,0:17:39.29,Main,,0,0,0,,pretty feathers\Nof yours crimson?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.20,0:17:41.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.41,0:17:44.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.28,0:17:46.40,Main,,0,0,0,,So, scorpion blood\Nis blue, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.42,0:17:48.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Learn something new every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.41,0:17:50.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Lupin!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.28,0:17:51.31,Main,,0,0,0,,But how?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.41,0:17:58.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Then this blood came from---
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.43,0:18:01.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Scorpions that were\Nnesting inside the mummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.38,0:18:04.27,Main,,0,0,0,,So very sorry\Nto disappoint you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.31,0:18:08.39,Main,,0,0,0,,What the--?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.41,0:18:10.28,Main,,0,0,0,,What's happening now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.30,0:18:11.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.38,0:18:14.29,Main,,0,0,0,,A blue-feathered peacock\Nmeans that death is near.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.31,0:18:15.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.26,0:18:16.39,Main,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.39,0:18:21.24,Main,,0,0,0,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.26,0:18:23.28,Main,,0,0,0,,The Laughing Peacock!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.30,0:18:27.31,Main,,0,0,0,,It's sculpted entirely\Nout of alexandrite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.33,0:18:28.35,Main,,0,0,0,,It's huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.37,0:18:30.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Makes the Smithsonian's\Nsixty carat stone
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.31,0:18:32.36,Main,,0,0,0,,look like a worthless pebble.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.38,0:18:35.39,Main,,0,0,0,,This is the actual\NLaughing Peacock.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.41,0:18:38.33,Main,,0,0,0,,So much for blue feathers\Nand certain death!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.35,0:18:41.40,Main,,0,0,0,,We're looking at\Nred feathers and big riches!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.31,0:18:51.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Ew!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.43,0:18:53.41,Main,,0,0,0,,No you don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.43,0:18:55.30,Main,,0,0,0,,That's my peacock!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.30,0:19:00.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.41,0:19:02.40,Main,,0,0,0,,We're about to be\Nburned to a crisp here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.29,0:19:05.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.40,0:19:07.41,Main,,0,0,0,,It should have a secret exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.43,0:19:10.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Traps like this one pretty\Nmuch always do, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.41,0:19:12.27,Main,,0,0,0,,That way the builders\Ndon't have to worry
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.29,0:19:15.43,Main,,0,0,0,,about whoever commissioned\Ntrying to seal them inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.21,0:19:17.34,Main,,0,0,0,,And sure enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.36,0:19:19.29,Main,,0,0,0,,There it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.39,0:19:32.25,Main,,0,0,0,,It's just an air vent!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.27,0:19:33.42,Main,,0,0,0,,We can't get out through there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.20,0:19:35.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't get hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.33,0:19:37.20,Main,,0,0,0,,This wall opens up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.22,0:19:38.36,Main,,0,0,0,,See, there's a keyhole.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.38,0:19:40.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.39,0:19:42.31,Main,,0,0,0,,It's shaped like--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.33,0:19:43.26,Main,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.28,0:19:44.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't even think about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.38,0:19:47.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Do you know how much work\Nit took me to get this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.26,0:19:48.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.34,0:19:52.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Alexandrite turns blue\Nwhen it's hit by sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.29,0:19:54.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Just give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.23,0:19:56.30,Main,,0,0,0,,It's only a red-feathered,\Nfortune-bestowing peacock
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.32,0:19:58.39,Main,,0,0,0,,while it's inside the pyramid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.41,0:20:01.29,Main,,0,0,0,,I guess you could choose to be\Nlocked up in here with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.31,0:20:04.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Then you could be\Na legendary peacock, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.31,0:20:16.21,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll give you another chance\Nif you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.23,0:20:18.30,Main,,0,0,0,,You do want me, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.32,0:20:20.23,Main,,0,0,0,,How about the\NSmithsonian's stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.25,0:20:22.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Sixty carats\Nis still pretty big.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.26,0:20:23.26,Main,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.28,0:20:25.20,Main,,0,0,0,,The bar's just\Nbeen raised even higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.22,0:20:27.32,Main,,0,0,0,,I hope you don't\Ndisappoint me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.21,0:20:31.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Maybe letting her stay\Nin there and be a peacock
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.25,0:20:33.29,Main,,0,0,0,,would've been\Nthe better option.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.31,0:20:35.32,Main,,0,0,0,,For her and for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.34,0:20:37.28,Main,,0,0,0,,No matter where\Nthat woman goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.30,0:20:39.36,Main,,0,0,0,,she's always\Na beautiful peacock.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.38,0:20:42.31,Main,,0,0,0,,If that's the\Nkinda thing you're into.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.33,0:20:44.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, shall we go ahead\Nand settle this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.23,0:21:02.41,Main,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.43,0:21:04.31,Main,,0,0,0,,I think I can wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.33,0:21:06.27,Main,,0,0,0,,I won't forget, Mini-Magnum.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.29,0:21:07.33,Main,,0,0,0,,It's Jigen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.35,0:21:09.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Daisuke Jigen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.22,0:21:11.40,Main,,0,0,0,,That's a lot less memorable\Nthan the other name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.27,0:21:21.26,Main,,0,0,0,,A wild one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.21,0:21:28.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Fujiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.35,0:21:32.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Doesn't she know that when they\Nwant to, even peacocks can fly?
